<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-10T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-10T07:00:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P.W./560: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-10T21:00:00+09:00">October
                                    10, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 10—2:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1606. For the Secretary and the Under Secretary only. I learn from an
                            absolutely reliable source that the proposed forthcoming landing of
                            further Japanese forces in northern Indochina is for the purpose of
                            attacking Yunnan in order to sever the Burma route. This information
                            should be most carefully guarded.<note n="6" xml:id="d331fn1">For
                                substance of warning of probable reaction of the United States
                                Government to such landings, see memorandum of October 9 by the
                                Counselor of Embassy in Japan, <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_669">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol.
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 669</ref>. The Ambassador
                                in Japan reported to the Department concerning this warning in his
                                telegram No. 1601, October 10, 3 p.m. (740.0011 P.W./559).</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>